title._content: Ben Hall, 1863 / [carte de visite copy photograph] Freeman Brothers, Sydney

description._content: "Description of Ben Hall / About 28 years of age, 5 feet 9 / inches high, stout build (would / weigh about 13 stone 7 lbs) figure / erect, respectable appearance / light brown wavy hair, short / light beard thick but darker near / his throat and jaws, pleasing / expression of countenance, soft / grey eyes, handsome nose / inclined to be hooked and thin / compressed lips - sometimes / [wears] beard & whiskers and / sometimes only beard. / This is considered a good / likeness - / PG [Police Gazette] 1863 Page 350" -- inscribed in ink on reverse over the photographer's stamp Format: Photograph Find more detailed information about this photograph: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=442170 Search for more great images in the State Library's collections: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/search/SimpleSearch.aspx From the collection of the State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au
